I was thinking the French system (at least that's what we call it
here) of two ballots might be more interesting, not to mention a lot
less complicated.  If one candidate wins a majority on the first
ballot, e is elected.  Otherwise, a second vote is taken with just the
top two candidates from the first ballot, in a runoff election.  Only
problem is ties, but those can be dealt with.

As is it now, an Officer can be elected by a plurality, which makes
for odd dynamics when there are four or more candidates up for a
single Office.

