Steve Gardner wrote:
>
>>   +3.1.4: Then what's Presence?  Isn't that a vote?
>
>Technically, no, Presence is not a vote. It doesn't cost you
>a Voting Token to declare your Presence on a Proposal. 
>Declaring Presence is just like abstaining on a Proposal,
>while counting towards Quorum. Since the cheapest way to get
>a Proposal to fail is to get it to fail Quorum, declaring
>Presence has the effect of expressing very mild support for
>a Proposal; mild opposition would be expressed by not voting
>or declaring Presence on it at all.
>[cf. 1715]

To this I would add:

N.B.: Casting a Vote Against a Proposal may, paradoxically,
cause it to pass, by causing that Proposal to meet Quorum.
Keep a close eye on the voting to see if this is likely.

(Or is this something we should let new Players figure
out for themselves?)

Chuck

