Proto: Meaningful Zeitgeist

Now that votes are scarce and Interest is free, the Zeitgeist title and awards
are not very meaningful - who wants to waste a vote to vote against a proposal
just to prevent a Zeitgeist award and only one vote FOR by the proposer and the
rest declarations of presence does not seem to me to be worthy of Zeitgeist.  I
suggest the following fix:

Amend Rule 1047 by replacing the text:

      When an Interested Proposal Proposed by some Player is adopted
      with no votes cast AGAINST it, that Player is awarded the Patent
      Title of Zeitgeist.

with the text:

      When an Interested Proposal Proposed by some Player is adopted
      with no votes cast AGAINST it and at least two Players other than
      the proposer voting FOR it, that Player is awarded the Patent
      Title of Zeitgeist.

I picked "two Players other than the proposer" to get back some of the original
meaning of Zeitgeist, overwhelming support by the Agoran community.  I'm open
to suggestion on this.  Anyone think it should be even harder?

-- Crito


