Proto: Indulgence Scarcity

Amend Rule 1712 by replacing the following text:

      At the beginning of each Nomic Week, the Herald shall randomly
      distribute a number of Indulgences equal to the number of Blots
      executed in the past Week, less the number of Blots vacated in
      the past Week, among all Players:

with the text:

      At the beginning of each Nomic Week, if the total number of
      Indulgences held by all Players is less than the total number of
      outstanding Blots by two or more, the Herald shall randomly
      distribute a number of Indulgences equal to the number of Blots
      executed in the past Week, less the number of Blots vacated in the
      past Week, among all Players:

This will gradually bring Indulgence holdings back down to where they were
intended, with the possibility of that "hot-potato" Blot.  It is also
automatically self-adjusting when Players deregister while holding Blots or
Indulgences.

-- Crito


